According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global High-Purity Metallic Boron Market was valued at USD 360 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 390 million in 2025 to USD 597 million by 2031, exhibiting a CAGR of 7.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth due to the rapid expansion of the semiconductor industry, increasing demand for electric vehicles (EVs), renewable energy technologies, and the rising adoption of advanced electronic devices. High-purity metallic boron has become an essential material for semiconductor manufacturing, enabling precise p-type doping in silicon wafers required for next-generation electronics, power devices, and photovoltaic systems.
The growing global semiconductor industry remains the primary driver of market expansion. As chip manufacturers continue investing in advanced fabrication facilities to support technologies such as 5G, artificial intelligence (AI), Internet of Things (IoT), and high-performance computing, the demand for ultra-high-purity boron materials is increasing significantly. High-purity metallic boron, particularly 5N and 6N grades, plays a critical role in controlling electrical conductivity within semiconductor wafers, making it indispensable for producing modern integrated circuits and electronic components.
